# --- BLOCKCHAIN CONFIG (Updated for Docker) ---
# Use host.docker.internal to allow Docker to talk to Hardhat on your Windows host
RPC_URL="http://host.docker.internal:8545"

# The Private Key of the company wallet (Use the first one from your Hardhat console)
COMPANY_PRIVATE_KEY="0xac0974bec39a17e36ba4a6b4d238ff944bacb478cbed5efcae784d7bf4f2ff80"

# --- IPFS CONFIG (Pinata) ---
PINATA_API_KEY="your_api_key_here"
PINATA_SECRET_KEY="your_secret_key_here"

# --- SECURITY ---
JWT_SECRET="super-secret-key-change-me"
PORT=8080
```

### 3. How to get these values
* **`COMPANY_PRIVATE_KEY`**: When you run `npx hardhat node`, a list of "Accounts" and "Private Keys" appears in your terminal. Copy the **first private key** (Account #0) and paste it here.
* **`PINATA_API_KEY` & `SECRET`**: Log in to [Pinata.cloud](https://pinata.cloud/), go to the API Keys section, and generate a new key with "Admin" permissions.
* **`RPC_URL`**: Keep this as `http://host.docker.internal:8545`. This is the "bridge" that lets the Docker container talk to the Hardhat node running on your Windows machine.

### 4. Important Step
After you save this file, you **must** rebuild your Docker container so it can "see" the new variables:

```bash
docker compose down -v
docker compose up --build